# Messaging estate inventory

## Scope and reading key

| Item | Inventory rule | Receipt |
|---|---|---|
| Operator-facing | Includes proactive notices, gateway-agent replies, digests, command/UI replies, callbacks, reactions, and delivery receipts. iMessage is inventoried even though the brief excludes it from the first stream. | `.brain/projects/message-event-stream/message-event-stream-brief.svx:15-23,35-41,51-54` |
| Runtime surfaces | Covers the joelclaw monorepo, the active Flagg LaunchAgents that invoke message producers, the deployed observer release, and the AI Hero scoreboard producer. | `/Users/joel/Library/LaunchAgents/com.joel.verify-voice.plist:7-25`; `/Users/joel/Library/LaunchAgents/com.joelclaw.sms-vetting-check.plist:7-23`; `/Users/joel/Library/LaunchAgents/com.joelclaw.observer-neat-memory.plist:7-20`; `/Users/joel/Library/LaunchAgents/com.aihero.ads-warmup-scoreboard.plist:5-17` |
| “Current traffic” | `active` means a registered function, daemon listener, active LaunchAgent, or callable CLI/SDK path. `manual/lab` means code exists but no resident producer is wired here. | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/index.host.ts:27-104`; `packages/gateway/src/daemon.ts:5015-5425` |
| Privacy | This asset records schemas, IDs, routing, and aggregate call sites only. It contains no message bodies, actors, tokens, or secrets. The journal CLI is the private body-bearing reader. | `packages/cli/src/commands/messages.ts:59-64,88-148` |

## Producer lanes

### Canonical-looking lanes that still fork before delivery

| Lane | Producers and current traffic | Identity and correlation minted | Kind / priority declaration | Delivery path and receipt |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `notify send` compatibility lane | CLI command; SDK `notifySend`; satellite repair request; observer neat-memory; AI Hero ads scoreboard; SupportBench red alert; voice verification; SMS vetting; Restate contact enrichment; learner-flow action receipt; visible-delivery canary. Active CLI and three scheduled LaunchAgents. | CLI accepts a stable UUIDv4 `--event-id`, otherwise mints `crypto.randomUUID()`. It also mints legacy `flowId=notify:<eventId>` and an audit record. | Producer may declare `kind`; otherwise compatibility infers kind from source and `priority`. Priority remains in the Redis envelope. | Atomic Redis idempotency key + session lists/pubsub → Redis bridge → contract-v2 mapper → Chat SDK send → ClickHouse/outbox journal → Redis terminal projection → HATEOAS CLI envelope. | `packages/cli/src/commands/notify.ts:6-9,68-104,106-194`; `packages/sdk/src/capabilities/adapters/gateway-redis.ts:205-226,234-355`; `packages/gateway/src/chat-sdk/notify-compat.ts:17-50`; `packages/gateway/src/chat-sdk/notify-acting.ts:72-100,163-217` |
| Contract-v2 Chat SDK outbound | Today only the `notify send` acting bridge calls exported `send()`. No other composition-root caller was found. Active for Telegram and Slack; Discord adapter is configured off in the daemon. | Every send mints a fresh branded `flow_v2_<uuid>`. Producer supplies `correlationId`; compatibility sets it to `<source>:<notify-event-id>`. Platform returns `platformMessageId`. | Typed kind resolves through one table to platform, lane, urgency, and formatting. Current table still encodes priority lanes: memory/alert/ask → Telegram operator; digest → Telegram digest; receipt → Slack automation. | Requested journal row → route/policy → SDK adapter → confirmed/failed/suppressed/digested journal row → flow/message/action projections → delivery receipt. | `packages/gateway/src/chat-sdk/outbound.ts:536-578,643-817`; `packages/message-contract/src/flow-id.ts:1-12`; `packages/message-contract/src/routing.ts:13-48`; `packages/message-contract/src/receipt.ts:18-66`; `packages/gateway/src/channels/redis.ts:795-829` |
| `gateway/send.message` durable-function lane | Explicit emitters: daily token usage, NAS backup, ADR pitch, content review, wiki edition, signal reminder, queue observer, self-healing, VIP email, and VIP morning brief. Registered host consumer is active. | Inngest `event.id` becomes `audit.eventId`; absent producer flow becomes `flowId=inngest:<event.id>`. A SHA-256-derived journal revision is minted from source event ID. | No contract kind. Producer declares channel and optional audit fields. Some payloads carry their own priority-shaped metadata, but the queue contract does not enforce kind. | Inngest event → worker journals `delivery.queued` → Redis `joelclaw:outbound:messages` + pubsub → daemon deletes list before delivery → hand-rolled Telegram/Slack/Discord/iMessage adapters. | `packages/system-bus/src/lib/channel-delivery-audit.ts:6-47`; `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/gateway-send-message.ts:29-43,127-202`; `packages/gateway/src/daemon.ts:5080-5160,5190-5425` |
| Gateway middleware / `pushGatewayEvent` lane | Dozens of system-bus functions use `gateway.notify/progress/alert`; older functions call `pushGatewayEvent` directly. Active resident system-bus path. Complete call-site tables follow below. | `pushGatewayEvent` mints a fresh UUID each call. Type and source are producer strings. No stable semantic key is required. | No contract kind. Some payloads set `priority`; the Redis channel classifier decides immediate/batched/ingested/suppressed. | Redis session list/pubsub → compatibility bridge only if audit flow starts `notify:`; otherwise classifier → immediate Telegram, gateway prompt, digest batch, context-only ingestion, or silent suppression. | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/agent-loop/utils.ts:285-339`; `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/middleware/gateway.ts:151-245`; `packages/gateway/src/chat-sdk/notify-acting.ts:72-81`; `packages/gateway/src/channels/redis.ts:773-934` |
| Gateway agent-response lane | Responses from the resident Pi session, including replies to Telegram, Slack, Discord, and iMessage command-queue prompts. Active. | `OutboundEnvelope` carries no identity. Channel adapters call `createChannelDeliveryAudit`; if no audit seed exists, it mints a fresh UUID flow ID at send time. Telegram returns per-chunk platform message IDs. | No contract kind. Route follows source/channel; Telegram policy separately classifies and may suppress/digest. | Session event → outbound router → hand-rolled channel adapter. Telegram writes requested/confirmed/failed/unknown journal rows and OTEL. Other hand-rolled adapters do not share one canonical lifecycle. | `packages/gateway/src/outbound/router.ts:142-229`; `packages/telemetry/src/channel-audit.ts:70-88`; `packages/gateway/src/telegram-runtime.ts:1570-1650,1684-1885` |
| Redis outbound media lane | Pi gateway extension `/send-media` pushes `joelclaw:media:outbound` and publishes `joelclaw:notify:media-outbound`. Active daemon listener; extension only runs in central/satellite role. | Producer mints `media-out-<time>-<random>`; payload carries file path and optional caption. No flow, correlation, or idempotency key. | No kind or priority. | Daemon reads the whole list, deletes it before send, then calls hand-rolled Telegram media delivery. | `pi/extensions/gateway/index.ts:1177-1181,1771-1791`; `packages/gateway/src/daemon.ts:5015-5068` |
| Redis signal-digest lane | Non-contract gateway events classified as batched; heartbeat flushes hourly. Active. Noise-rate guard also appends investigation items to a separate signal-digest list. | Retains original random event IDs in batch rows; synthesized digest prompt has no semantic digest ID. Noise-rate guard uses timestamp-shaped `signalId`. | Classifier chooses `batched`; low-signal-only batches are silently suppressed. No message kind at append. | `joelclaw:events:batch` → destructive read/delete → optional suppression → one gateway agent prompt. Separate `joelclaw:telegram:signal-digest` is written by noise-rate guard. | `packages/gateway/src/channels/redis.ts:43-50,279-298,1296-1363`; `packages/gateway/src/heartbeat.ts:243-260`; `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/noise-rate-guard.ts:211-252,292-386` |
| Direct Telegram command/UI lane | Native command replies, pinned status, worktree controls, MCQ prompts, digest callback errors, and Discord MCQ components. Active inside gateway. | Provider message ID only, plus feature-local pending IDs/maps where present. No common flow/correlation ID and no common journal append boundary. | No message kind or priority. | Direct grammY/Discord.js API calls bypass contract v2 and most journal/projection logic. | `packages/gateway/src/commands/telegram-handler.ts:157,228,408,475`; `packages/gateway/src/commands/worktree.ts:41-53,298-345`; `packages/gateway/src/commands/mcq-adapter.ts:258,313,413`; `packages/gateway/src/commands/discord-mcq-adapter.ts:188,318-343`; `packages/gateway/src/digest-gateway.ts:427-439` |
| Direct Telegram stream lane | Token-stream updates and final chunks from resident Pi replies. Active. | Stream state owns Telegram message IDs; journal flow comes from channel audit when the stream path calls journal helpers. | No contract kind. | Direct `sendMessage`/edit calls; separate stream lifecycle and journal calls. | `packages/gateway/src/telegram-stream.ts:220-399,636-756` |
| Hand-rolled Slack / Discord / iMessage lane | Gateway agent replies and `gateway/send.message` queue can resolve all four adapters. iMessage is explicitly outside the first event-stream cutover. | Platform IDs are adapter-local; no shared required semantic key. | No contract kind for legacy queue/agent replies. | Daemon adapter selection calls `sendSlack`, `sendDiscord`, or `sendIMessage`; Discord and iMessage also expose standalone sends. | `packages/gateway/src/daemon.ts:5100-5143,5190-5218,5390-5402`; `packages/gateway/src/channels/discord.ts:692-695`; `packages/gateway/src/channels/imessage.ts:565-570`; `.brain/projects/message-event-stream/message-event-stream-brief.svx:51-54` |
| Direct infrastructure Telegram | Talon escalation calls Bot API directly. Restate and restate-lab ship separate Telegram adapters. Talon is active infrastructure; Restate channel traffic is manual/substrate-specific; restate-lab is lab-only. | Telegram `message_id` only. Restate channel adds its own callback action IDs, not message-contract flow IDs. | No contract kind or priority table. | Direct HTTP `sendMessage`, outside gateway journal, projections, and trace. | `infra/talon/src/escalation.rs:367-390`; `packages/restate/src/channels/telegram.ts:45-105`; `packages/restate-lab/src/channels/telegram.ts:26-61` |

